		<div id="comment_body_64771976"><p>There are many ways to make memory-safe code.  In simple terms instead of<br>pointer = system_call(allocate memory, size requested)<br>you add in some things like keeping track...of those things... that you originally figured the system would keep track of... like<br>array[allocations] add element (pointer, size, status)<br>pointer= system_call(allocate memory, size requested)<br>array[allocations] update pointer, size, and set status "allocated"</p><p>If you're using Rust it can do it all by itself, more like a<br>used to be malloc() bu<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
